    "inline_comments": [
      "Error codes that are safe to retry for non-idempotent send operations (e.g. sendMessage). These represent failures that occur *before* the request reaches Telegram's servers, meaning the message was definitely not delivered and it is safe to retry. Contrast with RECOVERABLE_ERROR_CODES which includes codes like ECONNRESET and ETIMEDOUT that can fire *after* Telegram has already received and delivered a message \u2014 retrying those would cause duplicate messages.",
      "Returns true if the error is safe to retry for a non-idempotent Telegram send operation (e.g. sendMessage). Only matches errors that are guaranteed to have occurred *before* the request reached Telegram's servers, preventing duplicate message delivery. Use this instead of isRecoverableTelegramNetworkError for sendMessage/sendPhoto/etc. calls where a retry would create a duplicate visible message."
